    <h1>Storage classes</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"contentLayout2">=20
<div class=3D"columnLayout single" data-layout=3D"single">=20
<div class=3D"cell normal" data-type=3D"normal">=20
<div class=3D"innerCell">=20
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">When none of the static PVs the <a hr=
ef=3D"https://wiki.intranet.uniper.energy/sales/pages/viewpage.action?pageI=
d=3D45089074" rel=3D"nofollow">HaCT</a>&nbsp;admin created match a user's P=
ersistentVolumeClaim, the cluster may try to dynamically provision a volume=
 specially for the PVC. This provisioning is based on StorageClasses:</span=
></p>
<p>We have different tiers of stoarge.</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);">Premium</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);">Standard</span><br><span style=3D=
"color: rgb(23,23,23);">&nbsp;you can also create a&nbsp;</span><em>Storage=
Class on your own</em><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);">. It</span><spa=
n style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);">&nbsp;defines the&nbsp;</span><em>reclaim=
Policy</em><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);">. </span><br><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">reclaim polic=
ies are -&nbsp; "Retain", "Recycle", and "Delete"</span></span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);">This reclaimPolicy controls the be=
havior of the&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);">underlying Azure s=
torage resource when the pod is deleted and the persistent volume may no lo=
nger be required. The underlying storage resource can be deleted, or retain=
ed for use with a future pod.</span></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23=
);">In&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://wiki.intranet.uniper.energy/sales/pages/view=
page.action?pageId=3D45089074" rel=3D"nofollow">HaCT</a><span>&nbsp;</span>=
 managed containers, 4 initial StorageClasses are created:</span></span></p=
>
<ul>
<li><strong>default&nbsp;</strong>- Uses Azure StandardSSD storage to creat=
e a Managed Disk. The reclaim policy indicates that the underlying Azure Di=
sk is deleted when the persistent volume that used it is deleted.</li>
<li><strong>managed-premium</strong>&nbsp;- Uses Azure Premium storage to c=
reate Managed Disk. The reclaim policy again indicates that the underlying =
Azure Disk is deleted when the persistent volume that used it is deleted.</=
li>
<li><strong>azurefile&nbsp;</strong>- Uses Azure Standard storage to create=
 an Azure File Share. The reclaim policy indicates that the underlying Azur=
e File Share is deleted when the persistent volume that used it is deleted.=
</li>
<li><strong>azurefile-premium</strong>&nbsp;- Uses Azure Premium storage to=
 create an Azure File Share. The reclaim policy indicates that the underlyi=
ng Azure File Share is deleted when the persistent volume that used it is d=
eleted.</li>
</ul>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23=
);">when no storage class is specified for a persistent volume, the default=
 stoarge class will be used, so that you need to ensure the appropriate sto=
rage for persistent volumes.</span></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23=
);">you can create a storage class using <strong>kubectl</strong></span></s=
pan></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23=
);">The below one is example for premium managed disks that specifies the u=
nderlying Azure Disk should continue to hold(retained) when the pod is dele=
ted.</span></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p>kind: StorageClass<br>apiVersion: <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"htt=
p://storage.k8s.io/v1" rel=3D"nofollow">storage.k8s.io/v1</a><br>metadata:<=
br>&nbsp; &nbsp; name: managed-premium-retain<br>provisioner: <a class=3D"e=
xternal-link" href=3D"http://kubernetes.io/azure-disk" rel=3D"nofollow">kub=
ernetes.io/azure-disk</a><br>reclaimPolicy: Retain<br>parameters:<br>&nbsp;=
 &nbsp; &nbsp;storageaccounttype: Premium_LRS<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;kind: =
Managed</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);">create and use a persisten=
t volume with Azure Files:</span></strong></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);">A storage class is used to define =
how an Azure file share is created.&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23=
);">A storage account is created in the resource group</span><span style=3D=
"color: rgb(23,23,23);">&nbsp;for use with the storage class to hold the Az=
ure file shares.</span></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);">below one is an example for Azure =
file storage class</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23=
);">you can name the file : azure-file-sc.yaml</span></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p>kind: StorageClass</p>
<p>apiVersion: storage.k8s.io/v1</p>
<p>metadata:</p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;name: azurefile</p>
<p>provisioner: kubernetes.io/azure-file</p>
<p>mountoptions:</p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- dir_mode=3D0777</p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- file_mode=3D0777</p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- uid=3D0</p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- gid=3D0</p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- mfsymlinks</p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- cache=3Dstrict</p>
<p>parameters:</p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; skuName: Standard_LRS</p>
</blockquote>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);">the below command creates the stor=
age class</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);"><strong>kubectl apply -f azure-fil=
e-sc.yaml</strong>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);">For more info on Azure files -&nbs=
p;</span><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://kubernetes.io/docs/conc=
epts/storage/storage-classes/#azure-file" rel=3D"nofollow">https://kubernet=
es.io/docs/concepts/storage/storage-classes/#azure-file</a></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,23,23);">refer to the url for storage class=
es:&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://kubernetes.io/docs/conc=
epts/storage/storage-classes/" rel=3D"nofollow">https://kubernetes.io/docs/=
concepts/storage/storage-classes/</a></span></p>
</div>=20
</div>=20
</div>=20
